3.00	Craig_Hummer	Craig Hummer	Craig B. Hummer (born in Akron, Ohio) is an American sportscaster known for his work on Versus (formerly OLN). He has covered the Tour de France since 2005, first as an interviewer and then in 2008 as an anchor alongside Bob Roll. Hummer is a former competitive ocean swimmer and lifeguard, winning titles and competing for NCAA Division III Kenyon College on an academic scholarship.	
